------------------------------------------------------Safvas looked up at his lord, “Yes Mi’Lord I did fail thee, “ stepping back to avoid the spiked tail of the pit fiend, “ but not all is lost. I have already bound with another on the prime material plane and I can use her as a anchor point for our gate!”<br>
<br>
“She will not expect this Mi’Lord,” Safvas smiled despite itself, “ her blood will fuel the return of our kind to the prime material plane! We will bring hell to Norrath Lord….”<br>
--------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Darkness: a moment in time before the truth is revealed… <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A> at: 5/31/01 7:18:54 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cac3ab><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/usafvas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Safvas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#c54400>(12/15/00 6:27:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Safvas returns from hell...</span><hr size=1> Only a twisting and a slight distortion of reality would have revealed the arrival of Safvas, had the eyes that should have been concerned been open, yet they slept in complete oblivion and innocence to what awaited them.  These eyes belong to a wonderful soul and soul so tasteful the nine hells quivered in anticipation.  <br>
<br>
“Master, awake sweet master,” Safvas whispered into Katreena’s ear, “awake lovely I have a gift for thee!”<br>
<br>
Jumping away from her warm succulent body Safvas watched her, watched below her skin and admired her healthy body, her healthy veins that pumped the blood that even now reinforced their bonding…  Hurting Safvas, would be felt by her now.   So much so he could depart most of his damage to her had he wished to!<br>
<br>
A smile crept across his face as Katreena began to stir.<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
So it begins...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BDF Officer</span><br>  Posts: 395<br> <font color=#c54400>(12/17/00 12:48:17 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katpix.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Safvas returns from hell...</span><hr size=1>     &quot;Was it morning?&quot; I asked myself disappointed that another day had come.  My aching heart had not ceased to pound nor had the tears seemed to ease the loneliness that had filled my being.  &quot;Yes, morning&quot; I felt the weight of my body fill my senses.  I waited to open my eyes to the world wanting to stay in the dream that I longed to be true. It was then that I sensed something else in the room.<br>
<br>
    I lay quietly eyes closed, breathing slowly waiting to hear any movement.  Memorizing the Fire Strike spell as to cast it at the intruder the moment I knew of his direction.<br>
I had expected Farvak's friends to take his revenge on me, since I was the one to bring about his capture.  His hate for me must now be as great as mine for him.<br>
<br>
    The air smelled of rain and electricity, a storm was approaching.  The room was cold and offered no physical comfort. &quot;Why was I so haunted by evil? I questioned again.  &quot;What was it that drew it to me, like a moth to the flame?&quot; I wanted so much to just go back to sleep and dream of Caddil and me forever together as it should have been. As Mother Tunare had promised. <br>
<br>
    Just then I heard the soft rush of sound as if wings were delicately brushing the air.  I stood up and cast at my target surprised him, &quot;Safvas&quot; I looked at him surprised for only a second. Then I felt my flesh blister and burn.  Quickly I cast heal on myself and stood back trying to make sense of this new situation. &quot;Had he cast on me?, No I did not see him do so?&quot; <br>
<br>
    He smiled as his eyes found the questions that were in my eyes.  He spoke &quot;You catch on quickly, Katreena.  Do not attempt that again.  You will suffer all of my wounds and pain, you have been warned&quot;.  <br>
  <br>
    My mind spinning trying to find some understanding to questions that I didn't want the answers to. &quot;How, why for what purpose&quot; I needed time to think.  I sat down on the bed and tried to wake myself up.  This had to be one of my nightmares, I was still dreaming, right?!  <br>
<br>
    I closed my eyes and laid back down, covering myself trying to close out the reality of the moment.  Whispering with a quivering voice &quot;Go away&quot;. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
     <p>Your very own Spam Girl & Adventurous Woodelf <BR>Katreena Wanderheart 42nd Leaf Master Brewer <BR>
<a
herf=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/"target="web"><img src="http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katreena.jpg" border="0"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A> at: 12/17/00 12:03:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cac3ab><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uwarrenla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarrenLa</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wizards.com/dnd/images/Elminster_sm.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Web-Master</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#c54400>(12/18/00 11:48:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Safvas returns from hell...</span><hr size=1> The pain was acute but tolerable. The loss of Safvas was a blessing. Safvas, O’Berton knew had broken the link between them and he was no longer a tool for the evil little imp. No longer did his blood boil when commanded by Safvas. Yes he was free of the curse and its bindings… <br>
<br>
Glancing about O’Berton knew the guild members had put him to death, but they had failed to cancel out his contingency magic, which whisked his soul away to his safe hold. There among the cold rocks waited four clones of him, now three remained as he stood up and began to rummage through the stored items he had placed here so long ago for just this occurrence. There on the bookshelf was his extra spell book. <br>
<br>
Returning to his secret tower in Kunark, O’Berton spent several days resting and gathering his thoughts. Slowly, overtime O’Berton began to remember the past, the past that Safvas had written for him. A past so deceitful O’Berton knew it would be a challenge to clear his name. Doing so would most likely mean his death at the very hands of the people he now needed to trust him if he was going to foil the plans of Safvas and its masters.<br>
<br>
Who or what did Safvas control now… O’Berton knew he must find this person for they had no idea the danger they now faced…<br>
<br>
<br>
~O'Berton <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukeleecresswell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelee Cresswell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif  BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 12/18/00 10:51:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukyalynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kya Lynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#c54400>(12/19/00 12:03:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Perspectives</span><hr size=1> &quot;Now Kygero!!&quot;, Katreena's mental voice rang in my head. I turned to Kaitlyne, dropping my hand in signal, she started her cast. &quot;COMBUST!!&quot;, Kaitlyne ended her spell and the door to where the evil Plague Bringers were meeting, burst into flaming splinters that shot far into the room. Without delay, the whole of the Bronze Dragon Fellowship that were amassing in Highkeep, stormed into the room, weapons whistling through the air in deadly efficiency. Lord Tiggyr, the newly appointed leader of the Bronze Dragons lead the charge bringing down two Plague Bringer lackeys quickly. I rushed in right after him and targeted another of the lackeys, &quot;FIRESTRIKE!!&quot;, and my spell caught the dark elf, blasting his body into a memory. The room filled up instantly with BDF members coming through doors and windows, allowing no escape routes. Sure enough, O'Berton, Iszabelle, and the rest of the Plague Bringers were jumping up from the table they were sitting at to make plans, their chairs flying out behind them in disarray. Immediately the air was filled with magic and electrical power, the room gleaned in different colors as different spells went off and lights flashed. The sound of steel on steel and the battle cries that controlled them became a cacaphony blending with the chanting and the spells going off. I spotted Iszabelle in the process of casting one of her deadly spells, and i started toward her not taking my eyes away. With my Wraith Bone hammer in my hand i quickly closed on her, she stepped back and then she saw me moving her way. Iszabelle's hands began to move in front of her and the syllables of a spell falling from her lips, it was going to be close. I exerted my limit of speed and strength to get to her before she could finsh her spell, for i knew it would be a deadly one. Damn, my luck had run out. The evil witch had just about finished her casting and i was still too far away to strike. With an evil grin on her face, she held her outstretched hands with palms facing me towards my chest and was about to cry her spells trigger word when all of a sudden, she stiffened and lost her facial smirk. Moving up to where she stood i saw Katreena's arms snake around Iszabelle's neck and arm. Being much stronger, Katreena pinned her prisoner to the table. Lowering my hammer, i smiled, glad to see her ok and Iszabelle with her face being smashed into the marble table.<br>
Katreena looked up and smiled for the first time in a long time. Sloar and Gorsha came running up behind me as they saw Katreena, both of them screaming in glee to see our guild sister.<br>
Katreena yelled out, &quot;Time for reunion later. Sloar, Gorsha, the door at the end of the hall...&quot;, she motioned behind her to the lighted hallway from where she snuck up on Iszabelle. &quot;In the room there, you will find that rat Farvak. He is weak and wasted, but still dangerous. Go and get him, bring that filthy creature in here with everyone else!&quot;<br>
&quot;Yes mam!!&quot; both men replied in stereo. Sloar and Gorsha grabbed a couple of the other BDF members and went about capturing Farvak.<br>
I looked over to where O'Berton was and found that Lord Tiggyr was standing in front of the Plague Bringers leader with his sword tip at O'Berton's neck. Riversong, Tweani, and Calicer all standing around O'Berton poised to strike. The sounds of battle died down and the highly charged air began to disapate, Tiggry's voice was loud and commanding.<br>
&quot;O'Berton, evil wizard and planner of the BDF downfall, SURRENDER OR DIE!!&quot;<br>
Smartly and to my disappointment, O'Berton lowered his hands and strained a smile. Holding his head high and straightening his robes, he spoke, &quot;I surrender.&quot;<br>
All the Plague Bringers dropped there weapons and waited to be bound and lead away. <br>
Katreena finished her bindings on Iszabelle and gave her to the BDF's that were charged with the jailing of the prisoners, the whole time Iszabelle screaming at the top of her lungs, &quot;This is not over Katreena, i will get you yet!! I will be back for you one day!! Wait and seeeee....&quot; then she was ushered out the door to be put behind bars.<br>
&quot;Excellent job sis, you performed with great courage and strength of spirit!! I commend thee!!&quot;<br>
&quot;Thx Kyg, i just obeyed the will of Mother Tunare and she gave me the strength to see it through.&quot;<br>
&quot;Agreed Kat, but she chose you cause of your strength and faith.&quot;, i replied.<br>
&quot;O.k., o.k., lets just go before they bring Farvak out, i really dont want to see his face ever again.&quot;<br>
&quot;Alright Katreena, let's go get cleaned up and we will talk later.&quot; At that time, Mythias and Kaitlyne both walked up behind me.<br>
Katreena started for the door, &quot;See you later Kygero! and thank you both for your help as well.&quot; She bowed to Kaithlyne and Mythias both.<br>
Mythias grinned showing all his pointy teeth, &quot;You are mossst welcome, guild sssissster of Kygero Keibugami.&quot;<br>
&quot;It was our pleasure Katreena of the BDF!&quot;, Kaitlyne finished and bowed in return.<br>
<br>
Next thing i know, everything is black... i see a point of light off in the distance, It grows larger until the brilliance of light is to intense to look at. I lower my eyes and then i hear a voice coming from the light.<br>
&quot;The witch Iszabelle was correct in her assumption, it is NOT over yet. The evil and destuction is just begining, you must prepare and watch closely the changes that occur all around you and everyone in Norrath. Be careful young druid.&quot;<br>
The light went out and reality set in again.<br>
I sprang up from my bed, sweating profusely realizing i was dreaming of the past couple days events. Remembering the voice, i knew i would never forget it.<br>
I got up from my slumber and splashed some cold water on my face. Brushing my hair out and putting clean clothes on, i went to Katreena's room to check on her. She had been sleeping alot and finally getting her chance to mourn her losses. When i turned the corner to the hall where her room was i heard her scream out, &quot;FIRESTRIKE!&quot; and then the blast of the spell effect. I bolted for the door and as i got to it i heard her cast her healing spell. The commotion died away, so i decided to wait a sec and listen. After a few minutes i heard her say, &quot;Go away!&quot;<br>
Did she know i was there at her door? Hmmm, i had to try. I knocked on her door softly. &quot;Sis, you ok? Can i come in?&quot;<br>
&quot;NO, just go away. Please go away.&quot; Katreena sounded distressed still, i would give her some more time.<br>
&quot;I will leave you alone Kat, but i'm coming back later. I need to discuss some things with you. Rest easy sis.&quot;<br>
I left her to her mourning and went to find Kaitlyne and Mythias. I went to the kitchen as i wanted to find something to eat. On my way down the stairs, i ran into Lady Kuvanu.<br>
I bowed to her, &quot;M'Lady, greetings to you this day. How fares thee?&quot;<br>
Kuvanu smiled and quietly spoke, &quot;Greetings to you Kygero and i am feeling most lightened now that the evil ones were put to death. Although i am surprised that Katreena had not come to see Farvak's execution.&quot;<br>
&quot;Yes M'Lady, i do not believe Katreena wanted to ever lay eyes upon him again, she is happy with the ending though, to be sure. She just needs more time, she was put through one heavy ordeal that tested her whole being.&quot;<br>
&quot;That is why i am glad i caught you alone here. You are going to the dining quarters i take it?&quot; Lady Kuvanu asked.<br>
I nodded to her, yes.<br>
&quot;Let us go together then.&quot;<br>
&quot;Yes M'Lady.&quot;, i responded.<br>
While i prepared some simple food stuffs of berries, cheeses, bread and grabbing the bottle of elvin wine, i poured us a glass while Kuvanu began.<br>
&quot;Listen Kygero, i know you have been doing everything you can to keep us informed and you were instrumental in the bringing down of the Plague Bringers. You and your Sister Kaitlyne as well as the Iksar, Mythias, did a remarkable job and it is greatly appreciated by all your guild sisters and brothers. Alas, that is why i come to you instead of anyone else. I need you to continue watching over Katreena as she gets her spirits back and becomes one with herself again. We are afraid for her sanity and health. Yes we know she is strong and will more than likely be fine, but keeping an eye on her would be advisable. Will you do this for me please?&quot; she took a sip of her wine.<br>
Gulping down the remnants of the berries, i responded, &quot;Of course M'Lady, i could think of nothing i would prefer to do. Katreena is in need of friends and her guild family right now. Think nothing of it, it will be done!&quot;<br>
Kuvanu stood, &quot;Good, thank you Kygero. Now i must be off. There are many things i have to do today. Take care and i will talk with you later.&quot;<br>
I got up from my chair and wiped my mouth with a cloth napkin. &quot;I understand M'Lady, be well.&quot; I bowed again to her as she departed.<br>
Cleaning up my small mess, i went to find Kait and Mythias. It was time to go to work again soon. We will have to try and keep grouped with Katreena for the next few weeks and maybe longer. I wished Gorsha hadn't have left right after the capture of the Plague Bringers. I missed him already.<br>
&quot;Tunare watch over us all.&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cac3ab><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BDF Officer</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#c54400>(12/19/00 11:14:12 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katpix.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   From the ashes </span><hr size=1>    Safvas whispered with a hiss &quot;Get up girl! Your being foolish now, we have no time for this&quot;.  I felt my blood burning inside me, my mind fighting for control of my actions as I rose from the bed.  &quot;Oh be this a spell Of binding evil&quot; I spat at him. &quot;What makes you think I would not gladly die than to do your bidding&quot;.<br>
 <br>
   Safvas answered his voice amused &quot;How can I let my master suffer death&quot; <br>
 <br>
    Just then a knock broke the moment &quot;Are you alright?&quot; I quickly responded &quot;No Please go away&quot;.  My mind twisting with the thought that Safvas could kill my own family with my own hand terrified me.  I had to find out how this Imp gained such powers over me and I had to find out quickly.<br>
<br>
    I turned to him my eyes flamed with anger my voice low but defiant &quot;If Farvak could not control me what makes you think that you can do so, wicked one.  I am not to be controlled by anyone or thing and certainly not by you!&quot;<br>
 <br>
    I found my clothes and pulled them on quickly my actions were not the graceful ones of habit but rough and shaky.<br>
<br>
