</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ada07e><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ukatreena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katreena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BDF Officer</span><br>  Posts: 528<br> <font color=#c54400>(1/19/01 5:54:17 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soyouthinkiam/eq/Kat/images/Katpix.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Return to O'Bertons</span><hr size=1> A storm had come up over High Hold Pass not uncommon for the mountain top.  Lightning flashed across the dark sky as if trying to shout out to me to leave this place and never return.  As we walked along the path under camouflage I let my mind seek out Slaor for any news of Kygero.  In actuality I was seeking out anyone that was family or friend.  <br>
<br>
My heart had grown heavy with the thought that I was returning to such a battle.  Salvas and Farvak had taken their toll on my spirit and even with the break to Nektulos forest I was feeling more than venerable.  The only hope I had of keeping the forces of evil at bay was the information that O'Berton had supplied to me.  I was still unsure that I had been given a gift or a trap.  As we closed in on our destination I found my mood to change from apprehensive to dark and irritable.  Farvak seemed more than cheerful enough as we arrived. <br>
<br>
I took my leave and headed to the Study in hopes to keep my mind from analyzing the situation.  I was more than disappointed to find Salvas there grinning with that all knowing smirk to watch over my every move there.  I turned and left to go to my bedroom.  <br>
************************************************************<br>
<br>
Salvas argued with Farvak &quot;She will not be under my control if you take her from my side.  However, I can always find her and bring her back should you, shall we say, lose her&quot; <br>
<br>
 Farvak said &quot;Salvas, look this will give you the secrecy you need to move the chest and she will be grateful to me for taking her out of here to her beloved forest even for a short time.  A kill two wolves with one arrow so to speak move&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;Okay&quot; Salvas agreed &quot;However, let me warn you if you make one mistake it is your life you forfeit here Farvak&quot;   Farvak waved him off saying &quot;yes, yes, yes and I will pay dearly been there done that. So what is new&quot;.  <br>
<br>
It wasn't till Farvak saw Bowszer that he had his moment of truth.  He thought to himself &quot;Shit, who the hell is this big obnoxious troll and how the hell does he know Kat? Great just great, Kat's friend so if I kill him, I blow it with Kat and Salvas. Damn it all. Just get her away from him for now and deal with this later&quot;<br>
<br>
The rest of the journey went without a hitch still the Troll had thrown Farvak  for a loop.  &quot;What would this little slip cost me&quot; he thought. But the incident was soon forgotten with the return to High Hold Keep.<br>
<br>
Kat seemed a bit edgy but that was to be expected now she had had a taste of freedom from the work she was so diligent to carry out.  Farvak thought as he watched the wood elf &quot;A wild free thing like a Fay Drake so beautiful you wanted to possess it for your own however to possess it would kill it.  Yes this did describe Kat.  However there was one person who did just that,Caddil.  How ever did he get her to  marry him?.  He was strong, and served the light, but what had he done that had caught Kat like a moth to a flame?&quot; Farvak couldn't for the life of him understand.  <br>
<br>
After things where settled Farvak knew he had to report to Salvas so off to the Study to bring Kat some wine that was tainted with herbs to make her sleep. This allowed Salvas and Farvak to make plans and carry them out without Kat becoming suspicious of their movements.  She was smart and very aware of all that was going on around her. <br>
<br>
