   I had mindlessly undressed my clothing lay at my feet, I stood naked to the storm waiting for the rain.  A chilly breeze blew gently across my face and brought goose bumps to my skin and still I stood there waiting.  Another flash across the sky another roll of thunder and still no rain fell. The air tingled with the promise of rain, the very ground seemed to beg for it.<br>
