<br>
I opened my eyes wide with the mention of his name.  I  looked around quickly assessing my new surroundings. I moved quietly, getting dressed, I discovered I was in a tent comfortably set up for a long stay.  Warm furs covered the beds and chest of simple necessities were  used as tables.  I looked around to find a weapon that I might use against any danger or enemy, none was to be found.<br>
<br>
 It was she that was surprised as she stepped in and discovered that I was up and awake. &quot;Well, Hello there! Good to see your up.  Come out and eat when your ready&quot; She said with a grin.  She backed out and called over her shoulder &quot;You can take a bath later, I will show you where&quot;  <br>
<br>
I straightened my clothing and put my hands through my hair to comb it out as best I could as I stepped out of the tent.  My eyes opened wide with delight, I breathed in the sweetness that was the Lesser Faydark, &quot;Mother Tunare bless me, I am home.&quot; I thought.   I sighed and stiffened my resolve as I watched the three women at the fire.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Good marrow to you ladies&quot; I greeted.<br>
 <br>
They were all three high elfs from the city of Felwithe, all bore a resemblance to each other.<br>
<br>
  &quot;My name is Katreena Wanderheart of Kelethin&quot; I introduced myself.  <br>
<br>
They bowed their heads in my direction and I returned the nod.  Their clothing was not of the fine silken robes of their fellow Felwithians, but leathers such as mine.  They had the look of  women who could take on even the toughest of warriors. <br>
<br>
&quot;My name is Kayla and these are my sisters&quot; the more formidable of the three said with a grin. &quot;Come warm yourself by the fire and have a bite to eat&quot; she welcomed me. <br>
<br>
The other two looked my way, not one of welcome but not a threat either, more one of distaste.  I was a Woodland Elf and these were High Elfs,  I was considered to be beneath their kind. I approached apprehensively not wanting to offend my hostesses.<br>
<br>
 I ate quietly and watched the three women wondering what had lead them to live in the forest, for this way was not the way of the High Elfs of Felwithe.  They lived in one of the most beautiful cities on Faydwer.  Marble halls and well dressed, wealthy men and women all, all of good blood and standing. <br>
<br>
 It was Kayla who spoke first &quot;Oh were are my manors.  I am Kayla Nybright we are the treacherous Nybright sisters of Felwithe. Our father is shamed by our actions as thieves. He has declared us dead to him&quot; she said with a laugh to her voice. <br>
<br>
My eyes opened wide when Kayla said that they were the Nybright Sisters.  I said &quot;Your father offers a reward for your deaths there is a price on your heads.&quot; <br>
<br>
 They all turned and then snickered &quot;You have heard of us then?&quot; <br>
 <br>
I answered   &quot;Oh, I spoke with your father, who asked that I kill you and return your pearls.   I was shocked by his words to say the least.  What kind of father would do such a thing to his own daughters.  I do not blame you for your fall, but him!&quot;<br>
<br>
Our eyes met and then we all laughed, music filled the forest like birds singing.  &quot;Well then, should we watch our back with you Druid?&quot; Kayla said half  teasingly. <br>
<br>
 &quot;No, but your father should be watching his&quot;  I chuckled &quot; I think your father should be the one that is hunted down like the dog he is.&quot;   They all nodded in agreement and smiled at me. Kayla said &quot;Welcome, Katreena you do us honor by staying with us for a time&quot;  <br>
<br>
 I replied &quot;I am so honored by your generosity&quot; and bowed to each. &quot;What may I do to help you tend your camp. <br>
<br>
 Kayla smiled and said &quot;You are to rest here and regain your strength Kat. That is all we ask of you.  For in doing that you will insure that Farvak will pay us well&quot; <br>
<br>
With the mention of Farvak's name I stared down into the fire and grew silent again.<br>
<br>
  It was Kayla who spoke next.  &quot;Now about that bath It will be cold but at least you will be clean.  Follow me&quot;   I got up and did as she bid me.  Quietly through the familiar forest to a pond. <br>
<br>
 &quot;I will be close by, should you need anything&quot; Kayla offered.  I shook my head yes that I understood that I would be watched discreetly.  <br>
<br>
I undressed  and dove into the cold water, the feeling was sensual as the water caressed my body.   I loved the water, to swim was to free my body from its own weight.  Washing the dirt of the last few days from my skin, I smiled for the first time in days.  I relaxed and let the water hold me as I floated lightly to the top. Looking up into the deep of the blue ski I closed my eyes and let go of all thoughts.<br>
<br>
&quot;Kat&quot;  came a whisper, as a hand touched my body.  I opened my eyes startled by the touch.  Only to look up into Farvak's eyes, deep and longing, his lips curved in a smile. Nothing else was said.. I put my arms around his neck and pulled myself to him, his chest warm against mine I looked into his eyes seeing him welcome my touch.  <br>
<br>
I whispered seductively &quot;Is this what you want&quot; as I let my fingers make slow circles down his back.  I gently kissed his lips biting at them softly. <br>
<br>
He sighed &quot;Yes as his hands moved me closer to him&quot; I backed away and grinned teasingly and turned around in the water slowly.<br>
<br>
  Then spat with all the  hate, fire and rage  I  had possessed  &quot;Good! because you will never have me like this, Never!&quot;.  I returned to the shore gabbed my clothes and stomped off to the tents. <br>
<br>
<br>
Kayla walked down into the water and snickered slyly at Farvak &quot;Well, I see what you mean by spirit!  Now that your hungry may I fulfill your desires for now.&quot; <p><img border="0" src="http://www.goodnet.com/~saxon/full-logo.gif"><img border=0 src=http://bronzedragonsite.homestead.com/files/tags/katreena.gif><BR>
