<br>
&quot;How dare you tease me like that! I should have killed you when I had the chance!&quot; Kayla screamed while Fravak walked away. She threw a large rock at him, just missing his head by inches.<br>
<br>
Fravak turned and, still tucking in his shirt, said &quot;I know you love to be teased. It's a good thing your aim is still as bas as always.&quot; Kayla threw another rock at him, missing by over a foot.<br>
<br>
He picked up his pack, ducked another rock, and quickly headed down the trail towards Steamfont. Kayla was still screaming behind him. He was still daydreaming about her soft skin and painfully sharp fingernails when he arrived at the pass to Steamfont. Shortly, Fravak arrived at the entrance to Ak'Anon.<br>
<br>
&quot;Halt human! You are not welcome here.&quot; the two guards, barely taller than Fravak's knees, blocked the entrance.<br>
Fravak resisted the urge to strangle the nearest guard and, instead, showed him the medallion that hung from his neck. The guard gasped and backed away from the entrance. <br>
<br>
&quot;That's more like it. Try to stop me again and Meldrath himself will drag you to his lab.&quot; The guards glowered but kept their distance. Fravak entered and demanded to the nearest clockwork that it take him to the necromancer's guild at once. <br>
<br>
&quot;Iszabelle was a fool to trust in you&quot; the small skeleton sitting across the table from Fravak said in an errie voice. &quot;What makes you think I will follow that same path?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;My lord, Iszabelle's own selfish plans brought her down. She severely underestimated the power of the Bronze Dragons. I know you would not make that same mistake.&quot; Fravak stared into eyes of death itself but did not look away.<br>
<br>
&quot;You will fail as she did if you aren't careful&quot; the skeletal figure hissed. &quot;You will have my allegiance as long as it suits my plans, but you first must bring me the research notes Iszabelle used to create the plague she tried to unleash on the Bronze Dragons.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Those notes were taken to Highkeep! It will take weeks to travel there. My lord, may I humbly ask for transportation to shorten the journey.&quot; Fravak wished Katreena could have taken him, but he could tell she still needed time to recover. He didn't have anything to threaten her with to make sure they had safe passage.<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well. You shall travel with the dead.&quot; The skeleton held out a finger and Fravak reached forward to touch it. Fravak screamed as the icy cold pain shot through his body and reached his heart. His last vision before the darkness grew and his heart stopped was that of the table rushing up to hit him in the face. <br>
<br>
As suddenly as it started, the pain disappeared. Fravak opened his eyes and, although there was no light, he could see the walls of a sewer cast in an errie violet glow. Slowly, he reached a hand up and put it on his chest. Fear overtook him as he realized his heart was not beating. &quot;Yer Dead! Stop looking so scared.&quot; said a gnome who was working at a nearby table. &quot;You'll come back to life soon enough.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Where am I?&quot; Fravak asked as he sat up. He looked down and noticed he was floating half an inch above the table.<br>
<br>
&quot;Freeport. In the Master's guild.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;He did it then. I must be going.&quot; Fravak grinned and got up off the table, realized he had been in this area of the sewers before.<br>
<br>
Fravak traveled swiftly and without fatigue as he crossed the Eastern Commons. Passing a small orc camp, he began to feel a tingling in his arms. He was comming back to life and needed to sit down. Confulsions overtook him as he started to breath again. Soon, his vision cleared enough to see the figures in front of him. A fierce battle between a band of orcs and a group of dwarves and high elves was underway. Fravak blinked a couple of times and realized he knew one of the dwarves. A young recruit of the Bronze Dragon Fellowship named Mikeybigarms. <br>
<br>
Still feeling weak from returning to life, Fravak shot Mikey an evil grin and continued on his way. Soon, he would have to come back and teach this young dwarf about the mistake in joining the Bronze Dragons.<br>
<br>
Upon reaching Highpass, Fravak found the notes and used the last of the money Safvas had left to purchase a teleport to Greater Faydark. Stepping into the shadows, he headed back to Castle Mistmoore to tell Safvas about the deal and to secretly duplicate Iszabelle's notes.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Where have you been?&quot; Safvas demanded even before Fravak had closed the door to the study. &quot;You couldn't have spent a week with those gnomes! Did they agree?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;No. They refused to join in your petty quest. Looks like we're on our own.&quot; Fravak could feel his blood begin to boil at Safvas's probing and resisted as best as he could. &quot;Get out of my head you stinking Imp. I have nothing to hide from you. I will talk to them again soon.&quot; Fravak tried to change the topic. &quot;How is Katreena doing?&quot;<br>
<br>
That seemed to work. &quot;She is doing much better and was seen this morning laughing at the campfire with Kayla.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Good. Maybe I should go pay her a visit.&quot; Fravak's eyes were filled with lust as he left the study. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbronzedragonfellowship75394stories.showMessageRange?topicID=78.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbronzedragonfellowship75394stories.showMessageRange?topicID=78.topic&start=41&stop=48>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbronzedragonfellowship75394stories.showPrevMessage?topicID=78.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbronzedragonfellowship75394stories.showNextMessage?topicID=78.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbronzedragonfellowship75394stories.threadControl?topicID=78.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbronzedragonfellowship75394stories.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=78.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbronzedragonfellowship75394stories.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=78.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub5.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="bronzedragonfellowship75394frm13">Picture Gallery<option value="bronzedragonfellowship75394flames">Flames<option value="bronzedragonfellowship75394announcementreadonly">Announcements<option value="bronzedragonfellowship75394events">Events<option value="bronzedragonfellowsh